CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 12, 1957, pg. A14 reads: "Carver Committee Meets - The 1958 committee for Carver Week met in Board of Education Building to complete plans for the annual observance Jan. 1-7. Seated are: Dr. Elizabeth Graf, general chairman; Mrs. Alma Illery, president, Achievement Clubs Inc., and Miss Marie A. Saul.  Standing: J. Allen Figural, treasurer; Mary K. Marshall, financial secretary; Goldie Hamilton, secretary, and the Rev. B.S. Mason. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Carver Week committee, seated, from left: Dr. Elizabeth Graf, Alma Illery, and Marie A. Saul; standing: J. Allen Figural, Mary K. Marshall, Goldie Hamilton, secretary, and Rev. B.S. Mason, gathered in interior of Board of Education building with sculptures and drawings
